committing%20enormous%20amounts%20of%20capex%20to%20pursue%20their%20ambitions%20in%20the%20space.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20with%20CNBC%2C%20Siegel%20highlighted%20a%20key%20point%3A%20companies%20are%20spending%20unprecedented%20amounts%20of%20money%20to%20scale%20their%20AI%20programs%2C%20but%20it's%20possible%20that%20soon%20there%20will%20be%20much%20less%20expensive%20ways%20to%20power%20the%20technology.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20the%20biggest%20risk%20with%20AI%20isn't%20if%20it's%20going%20to%20work%2C%20I%20think%20it's%20going%20to%20work%2C%20but%20it%20can%20be%20done%20more%20cheaply%2C%26quot%3B%20Siegel%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20compared%20the%20current%20AI%20boom%20to%20the%20dot-com%20bubble%2C%20arguing%20that%20the%20most%20important%20takeaway%20from%20that%20era%20was%20that%20plummeting%20costs%20are%20among%20the%20top%20reasons%20the%20bubble%20ultimately%20popped.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20really%20caused%20the%20bust%20was%20that%20they%20figured%20out%20how%20to%20put%201%2C000%20times%20more%20data%20through%20the%20fiber%20optic%20cables%20they%20were%20laying%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20noted.%20%26quot%3BAll%20of%20a%20sudden%2C%20all%20the%20companies%20that%20were%20going%20to%20wire%20the%20universe%20said%2C%20you%20know%20what%2C%20we%20don't%20need%20that%20much.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESiegel%20raised%20the%20question%20of%20whether%20companies%20can%20continue%20scaling%20AI%20without%20spending%20billions%20of%20dollars%20on%20data%20centers.%20In%20his%20view%2C%20the%20answer%20is%20yes%2C%20and%20the%20result%20will%20be%20a%20poor%20return%20on%20investment%20for%20the%20company%20and%20ultimately%20investors.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20commentators%20have%20begun%20to%20express%20worry%20about%20the%20size%20and%20scope%20of%20the%20AI%20investment%20boom.%20In%20a%20note%20on%20Monday%2C%20Neil%20Shearing%2C%20group%20chief%20economist%20at%20Capital%20Economics%2C%20made%20a%20similar%20argument%20about%20the%20risk%20of%20companies%20overextending%20themselves.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20scale%20of%20current%20investment%20is%20comparable%20to%20past%20technological%20surges%20%E2%80%94%20from%20railways%20to%20the%20internet%2C%26quot%3B%20Shearing%20said.%20%26quot%3BAs%20history%20shows%2C%20booms%20like%20these%20almost%20always%20involve%20some%20degree%20of%20overreach.%20Some%20projects%20will%20fail%20to%20pay%20back%2C%20leaving%20investors%20nursing%20losses.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20the%20bullish%20mood%20and%20the%20optimism%20over%20the%20transformative%20power%20of%20AI%20endure%20among%20commentators.%20Shearing%20added%20that%20although%20many%20tech%20companies%20did%20not%20survive%20the%20dot-com%20bubble%20bursting%2C%20the%20fibre%20optic%20network%20that%20they%20left%20behind%20proved%20valuable.%20AI%20data%20centers%20may%20have%20the%20same%20impact.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20may%20look%20like%20wasteful%20investment%20from%20a%20financial%20standpoint%20%E2%80%94%20and%20indeed%20is%20a%20waste%20for%20some%20firms%2C%20with%20consequences%20for%20their%20investors%20%E2%80%94%20can%20be%20an%20important%20part%20of%20the%20economic%20diffusion%20process%2C%26quot%3B%20Siegel%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-bubble-dot-com-crash-data-centers-infrastructure-jeremy-siegel-2025-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1763408563000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F691b76bfabd5e944effae10a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-bubble-dot-com-crash-data-centers-infrastructure-jeremy-siegel-2025-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Wharton%20Economist%20Jeremy%20Siegel%20says%20a%20sudden%20plunge%20in%20the%20cost%20of%20powering%20AI%20is%20a%20risk%2C%20as%20companies%20pour%20billions%20into%20infrastructure.%22%2C%22auth